      <T n="text">0x6D0E6DB8<!--<font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Experience</b></font> is how a Fairy unlocks their full potential on the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Ability Tree</b></font>. Fairies can receive Fairy Experience by performing various Fairy-related activities, with the most beneficial being performing Fairy Abilities. They can also receive Fairy Experience by shrinking and interacting with objects or using <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Dust</b></font> to perform magic acts like <font color="#199C2C"><b>Enchanting Plants</b></font>. You also gain Fairy Experience from a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy's innate Abilities</b></font> like <font color="#199C2C"><b>Detecting</b></font> and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Absorbing Emotions</b></font>.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_FairyAbilitiesLevelingUp_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:de052b1bf5824e67</T>
      <T n="text">0xAF78371E<!--The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Ability Tree</b></font> has four paths: <font color="#199C2C"><b>Manipulation, Emotion, Nature</b></font>, and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Passive Abilities</b></font>. Highlighting an Ability will show an explanation of the ability, the Emotional Force cost, as well as where the Ability needs to be performed (such as on a Plant or another Sim). Some Abilities have two levels, like <font color="#199C2C"><b>Nurture Nature's</b></font> second level that unlocks the ability to <font color="#199C2C"><b>Enchant Plants</b></font>!\n\nPassive Abilities are not actively performed but happen throughout a Fairy's day-to-day automatically. Only one Ability may be selected per level, so choose wisely!--></T>
    </U>
